Pegas Nonwovens Gains to Month-High After Egypt Investment Plan

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-06-01T07:55:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/pegas-nonwovens-gains-to-month-high-after-egypt-investment-plan.html
Pegas Nonwovens SA (PEGAS)  gained for a third
day to its highest in almost a month after the Czech maker of
special textiles used in hygiene and health-care products said
it plans to build a new plant in  Egypt .  The stock rose as much as 0.6 percent to its strongest
intraday level since May 4, and traded up 0.4 percent at 452
koruna as of 9:49 a.m. in Prague.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  